Fix: ThorVG "config.h: No such file or directory" on Windows/MSYS2
=====================================================================

Problem:
  LVGL's built-in ThorVG library requires a config.h that is generated
  by cmake. On Windows/MSYS2, this file is not generated correctly,
  causing all ThorVG .cpp files to fail with:
    fatal error: config.h: No such file or directory

  This affects the original lv_port_pc_vscode from LVGL's repo.
  Our customized repo (lv_port_pc_vscode_aic-eec) already has this fix.

Solution:
  ThorVG is used for Lottie animations and vector graphics, which are
  not needed for the course examples. Disable it entirely.

Steps:
  1. Edit lv_conf.h - change these 3 defines to 0:

     #define LV_USE_LOTTIE          0
     #define LV_USE_VECTOR_GRAPHIC  0
     #define LV_USE_THORVG_INTERNAL 0

  2. Edit CMakeLists.txt - add this BEFORE the add_subdirectory(lvgl) line:

     # Disable ThorVG (causes config.h issues on Windows/MSYS2)
     set(CONFIG_LV_USE_THORVG_INTERNAL OFF CACHE BOOL "" FORCE)

  3. Edit CMakeLists.txt - remove lvgl::thorvg from MAIN_LIBS:

     Before: set(MAIN_LIBS lvgl lvgl::examples lvgl::demos lvgl::thorvg ${SDL2_LIBRARIES})
     After:  set(MAIN_LIBS lvgl lvgl::examples lvgl::demos ${SDL2_LIBRARIES})

  4. Clean and rebuild:

     rm -rf build
     mkdir build && cd build
     cmake -G "MSYS Makefiles" ..
     make -j
